    "title": "Here are the 2026 EU Prize for Contemporary Architecture winners",
    "link": "https://culture.ec.europa.eu/whats-new/news/here-are-the-2026-eu-prize-for-contemporary-architecture-winners",
    "pubDate": "2026-04-14T14:06:03.000Z",
    "content": "<html><head></head><body><h1 class=\"title-h1 eac-page-title\">Here are the 2026 EU Prize for Contemporary Architecture winners</h1>\n<span><span>csudaga</span></span>\n<span><time datetime=\"2026-04-14T16:06:03+02:00\" title=\"Tuesday, April 14, 2026 - 16:06\">Tue, 04/14/2026 - 16:06</time>\n</span>\n<div class=\"ecl\"><h2><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Winners of the 2026 EU Prize for Contemporary Architecture</span></h2><p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">On 16 April, the European Commission and the Fundació Mies van der Rohe announced that the winners of the 2026 EU Prize for Contemporary Architecture are</span></p><ul type=\"disc\"><li data-list-item-id=\"e9375046130bca5c35d761265f85118d8\"><p><span lang=\"EN-GB\"></span><span lang=\"EN-GB\">in the architecture category: Charleroi Palais des Expositions by AgwA and AJDVIV (Belgium)</span></p></li><li data-list-item-id=\"e342e533792969189e643601625aefd29\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\"></span><span lang=\"EN-GB\">in the emerging category: Temporary National Theatre by Vidic Grohar Arhitekti (Slovenia)</span></li></ul><p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">The 7 members of the international jury announced the winners in in Oulou (Finland), 2026 European Capital of Culture, after visiting the finalist works.</span></p><h2></h2></div></body></html>",
