  {
    "title": "New study recommends improvements for the discoverability of European cultural content online",
    "link": "https://culture.ec.europa.eu/whats-new/news/new-study-recommends-improvements-for-the-discoverability-of-european-cultural-content-online",
    "pubDate": "2026-03-31T14:03:18.000Z",
    "content": "<html><head></head><body><h1 class=\"title-h1 eac-page-title\">New study recommends improvements for the discoverability of European cultural content online</h1>\n<span><span>csudaga</span></span>\n<span><time datetime=\"2026-03-31T16:03:18+02:00\" title=\"Tuesday, March 31, 2026 - 16:03\">Tue, 03/31/2026 - 16:03</time>\n</span>\n<div class=\"ecl\"><p>A new study prepared for the European Commission details how discoverability has become the critical factor determining which cultural works can rise above the digital noise and be noticed, accessed, and engaged with by audiences.</p><p>The research, commissioned under the EU Work Plan for Culture 2023–2026, examines how European cultural content is discovered and accessed in today’s digital environment. &nbsp;The study introduces a new conceptual framework for understanding discoverability in the digital era, where interconnected elements work together to determine which works reach audiences and which remain hidden.</p><h2>A focus on music and books</h2><p>It provides detailed analysis of the music and book sectors, with insights into other cultural and creative sectors and industries affected by the increasing use of platforms and algorithms. The study analyses how di</p></div></body></html>",
